54.7	Flag_Day_in_the_United_States	Flag Day (United States)	In the United States Flag Day is celebrated on June 14. It commemorates the adoption of the flag of the United States, which happened that day by resolution of the Second Continental Congress in 1777. The United States Army also celebrates the Army Birthday on this date; Congress adopted "the American continental army" after reaching a consensus position in the Committee of the Whole on June 14, 1775.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/64/US_Flag_Day_poster_1917.jpg/225px-US_Flag_Day_poster_1917.jpg
